# alias

An object containing zero or more aliases used to replace values in import statements. These aliases are automatically passed to Vite and TypeScript.

You will need to run npm run dev to have SvelteKit automatically generate the required alias configuration in jsconfig.json or tsconfig.json .

```
/**@type{import('@sveltejs/kit').Config}*/constconstconfig:{kit:{alias:{'my-file':string;'my-directory':string;'my-directory/*':string;};};}@type{import('@sveltejs/kit').Config}config={kit:{alias:{'my-file': string;'my-directory': string;'my-directory/*': string;};}kit:{alias:{'my-file': string;'my-directory': string;'my-directory/*': string;}alias:{// this will match a file'my-file':'path/to/my-file.js',// this will match a directory and its contents// (`my-directory/x` resolves to `path/to/my-directory/x`)'my-directory':'path/to/my-directory',// an alias ending /* will only match// the contents of a directory, not the directory itself'my-directory/*':'path/to/my-directory/*'}}};
